Lucia rarely brings this up, but she actually cares about what you say. Lee is sometimes very blunt, but he cares about you as much as I do. As long as you and everyone are safe and sound, everything I've done will be worth it.
Prayers, oaths, and miracles are like causes and effects. What keeps me here with you still at this moment is the fierce wish I had in my heart.
If meeting you is a miracle, is this endless heat in my chest the price for it?

If there is an end to this war, what would you like to see? Farmlands, riverbanks, groves, seashore... We can go visit all the places we have yet to see together.

Conductor... Conductor... I can finally hear your voice. Please don't leave me alone in the silence...
Now I'm getting the hang of this job, even the maths that I used to hate so much... Oops, sorry, guess I was talking big...
Commandant, let me know if you need anything, okay? I'm confident with my strength.

Today, I'm going to challenge "playing hide & seek alone"! How can one person play hide & seek by herself? That's why I will never get caught. In other words, it's a game that Nanami is guaranteed to win... What, would you also like to play? Okay... Promise me that you will find me!

Danger...! Commandant, stand next to me—Hmph (realizes it was just a trick)... (Slightly ashamed for her own behavior, while debating whether she should criticize Commandant's action) Forget about it...

This is where I was abandoned when I was born, where my dream came to an end. But flowers and sunlight have given this place new memories, and when you're here, I can't help but wonder... how nice it'd be if time would stop, so that the one I miss could stay here in this moment.

When you weren't here, I could see that dream again—the one woven together from the data left behind. Its ending is changing little by little. Sometimes, it doesn't end at the church, and sometimes, the renegades aren't the enemies... The only thing that never changes... is that I always end up finding you. Perhaps that isn't what's calculated, but what I want.

Can't I be here if I have nothing to do? I just want a quiet place to calibrate my gun set. There are too many outsiders in the maintenance room. I'm not used to it.

What would I be doing if I hadn't taken up painting? Maybe I'd enroll in F.O.S. and become your schoolmate? Haha... I'm kidding. I've had so many precious and wonderful memories because I painted. To give them up for a different life... I'll never make that trade!

You've known me for so long that your painting skills must have improved, right? I guess that makes you my student, doesn't it? In that case, as your teacher, I shall give you your final exam—ahem... Commandant, can you paint a picture for me?

The secret of the Ascension-Network? Don't mind it too much. You won't find the path you've chosen there. I'll show you the consequence of your choices soon enough. But perhaps we are not so different after all...(Laughs) I meant the two of us—you and me, not Ascendants and Babylonia.
If you're tired, give up on everything and go away. Leave it all to me, whether you live, die by my hand, or just wander off... But... never surrender to me.

Hah, your petty tricks... I'm simply restraining my power right now. Don't think for a moment that you're getting stronger.

Sleep if you're tired. If you're brave enough to be in a room with an Ascendant, why would you be afraid of being reprimanded for slacking? Relax. No one will know what happens in this room apart from you and me.

If you're falling asleep, let me tell you a bedtime story—you won't be able to sleep after you hear it. Let me think… What story shall I tell you… Stop asking me why, unless you're not sleepy in the first place?
You're like a struggling caged bird, smashing and shaking your prison.

It's been a while. Perhaps I should put you on a leash in case you leave without a word... I'm kidding. No matter where you are, I'll still have my eyes on you. I won't let my most dangerous enemy out of my sight. I hope you're smart enough to do the same.
Oh, this? I'm just making my normal clothes. I can handle this! I just need to thread this needle first. Um, Commandant... would you mind threading this needle for me?

Alright, I think you really enjoy this... Anyway, please refrain from doing it to others, okay?

Welcome home, Commandant. You are... wearing a special look. What happened? We have a lot of time. Take a seat and tell me about it.

...I'm just measuring the size of this room. Somehow I just feel this room is large when I'm alone, but when I'm with you, it feels like just the right size.
I've never seen this childish side of you... Or are you feeling lonely?

Is my balancing device bothering you?
Do you miss Buddy too? ...Buddy is right here. I can feel it.
Hey. Give me your hand. Here. The pink sister from Gray Raven asked you to go out and get more sunlight, but you haven't been out, so I got some for you. Sunlight.

No! Tail! Stop! ...Huh? Nothing.

HA! That little secretary of Nikola's came over with a stack of papers, but one look, and I scared her away. You should be thanking me. What...? Something wrong with that?
Hey, cheer up! I like it when you smile more... Haha! There we go! That's more like it, Commandant!

Battle scars are a badge of honor. Injuries just come with the territory... It's nothing for a badass like me... B-but if you're worried, I-I'll be more careful. J-just don't give me that look again. Okay?
